    the name of Pliny the Younger.... On the basis of what follows at 507c ff.[?], it came to be used 
    (cf. [2] against [1]) for a collection of aphorisms [3] from late antiquity based on a Greek original 
    with the addition of 16 sayings of Publilius Syrus which, from the Carolingian epoch, became available 
